The registry shall adopt such regulations and official forms and perform such duties as are necessary to implement the provisions of KRS 61.710 to 61.780. The registry is authorized and empowered to:
Develop prescribed forms for the making of the required reports;
Prepare and publish a manual for the individuals subject to KRS 61.710 to 61.780 describing the requirements of the law, including uniform methods of reporting;
Permit copying or photocopying of any reports as requested by any person;
Ascertain whether any individual subject to the requirements of KRS 61.710 to 61.780 has failed to file a report or has filed a defective report, give notice to delinquents of failure to file the report, as provided in KRS 61.740;
Hold public hearings, investigate any violations in reporting, and issue subpoenas for the production of documents and attendance of witnesses.
